            <h3>What is Body Fat?</h3>
            <p>
                Body fat is the amount of fat tissue present in your body. It is necessary for various bodily functions, including:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Energy Storage:</strong> Fat serves as a long-term energy reserve that the body can tap into during periods of caloric deficit.</li>
                <li><strong>Insulation:</strong> Adipose tissue helps regulate body temperature by providing insulation against cold.</li>
                <li><strong>Protection:</strong> Fat cushions vital organs, protecting them from physical trauma.</li>
                <li><strong>Hormone Production:</strong> Fat cells produce hormones like leptin, which regulates appetite and metabolism.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                While some body fat is essential for health, excessive or insufficient body fat can lead to various health issues, including obesity, cardiovascular diseases, and hormonal imbalances.
            </p>
            
            <h3>Why is Body Fat Important?</h3>
            <p>
                Maintaining an appropriate body fat percentage is crucial for:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Overall Health:</strong> Balanced body fat levels reduce the risk of chronic diseases such as diabetes, heart disease, and hypertension.</li>
                <li><strong>Physical Performance:</strong> Optimal body fat enhances athletic performance, strength, and endurance.</li>
                <li><strong>Body Composition:</strong> Understanding body fat helps in achieving a lean and toned physique, essential for aesthetic goals.</li>
                <li><strong>Metabolic Function:</strong> Proper fat levels support metabolic processes and hormonal balance.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Regularly monitoring body fat can provide insights into your health status and help tailor your fitness and nutrition plans accordingly.
            </p>
            
            <h3>How is Body Fat Calculated?</h3>
            <p>
