                <li><strong>Gender:</strong> Females typically have higher body fat percentages than males due to hormonal differences and reproductive needs.</li>
                <li><strong>Genetics:</strong> Genetic factors can influence fat distribution and metabolism.</li>
                <li><strong>Diet:</strong> Caloric intake and macronutrient composition significantly impact body fat levels.</li>
                <li><strong>Physical Activity:</strong> Regular exercise helps in reducing body fat and maintaining muscle mass.</li>
